<paragraph id="750636CFFFB54A44FF35A3CB4D55FA9E" blockId="19.[151,1437,846,1339]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
New record for Madeira. The species appears to have been absent from Madeira until a few years ago. Since 
<number id="C37124E8FFB54A44FF2FA3B34F15FB49" box="[223,282,1234,1260]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2003.0">2003</number>
(if not earlier) it regularly appears in Funchal fish market (figure 
<number id="C37124E8FFB54A44FBD1A3B34A3FFB49" box="[1057,1072,1234,1260]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="7.0">7</number>
) and the fishermen state that it has been caught in Madeira waters. The first author has seen the species during a 
<collectionCode id="13A8AE0AFFB54A44FB8AA3984AD3FAB6" box="[1146,1244,1273,1299]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">SCUBA</collectionCode>
dive at Caniço, south-eastern coast of Madeira. 
<accessionNumber id="6AEAAB2CFFB54A44FDFEA2404CA9FA9E" box="[526,678,1313,1339]" httpUri="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/MMF35194" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
